\displaystyle \frac{1}{n+x} = \frac{1}{n}\left(\frac{1}{1+\frac{x}{n}}\right) = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{k \ge 0}\frac{(-1)^kx^k}{n^k} = \sum_{k \ge 0}\frac{(-1)^kx^k}{n^{k+1}}
\displaystyle \ln(x+n) = \sum_{k \ge 0}\frac{(-1)^kx^{k+1}}{n^{k+1}(k+1)}+\mathcal{C} 
